y data pending on a pty.<br /><br />Yes, it's "buggy" only in a QoI sense - I'm sure that if you read POSIX <br />and SuS like a language lawyer, there is absolutely zero that says that it <br />can't return EINTR at any random time, or that the SIGCHLD should be <br />ordered wrt the other side of the pty having done a write.<br /><br />But we don't do language-lawyering based on standards that inevitably <br />never really delve into all the nitty-gritty details. We are simply better <br />than that. Leave the language-lawyering to the people who can't do things <br />well, and then whine about their crap being "technically correct".<br /><br />			Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
